cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with solving parity games, which are formal games with omega-winning conditions, using algorithms based on Boolean Decision Diagrams (BDDs). 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of different algorithms for solving parity games. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper involves implementing algorithms in a programming language and comparing their performance. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as one of the algorithms discussed in the paper is based on automata. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as parity games have applications in verification and synthesis, which are areas of AI research.
